    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 134</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 2 gp <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d2 (small), 1d3 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> disarm, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Light; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Close</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>Also known as an iron claw, this device consists of a fanlike structure of three or more 10-inch blades secured to a sturdy handle strapped to the forearm of the off hand. It can be used as an offensive weapon or defensively like a buckler, or used to disarm an opponent without provoking an attack of opportunity. It provides its owner with a +2 circumstance bonus on attempts to disarm or sunder swords or other slender-bladed weapons.</p>",
